----ENDF/B-VIII.0     MATERIAL 58                                   58 1451     
-----THERMAL NEUTRON SCATTERING DATA                                58 1451     
------ENDF-6                                                        58 1451     
                                                                    58 1451     
 Temperatures = 296 400 500 600 700 800 1000 1200 deg k.            58 1451     
                                                                    58 1451     
 History                                                            58 1451     
 -------                                                            58 1451     
 this evaluation was produced at los alamos in 1993 using           58 1451     
 the same model as the ga evaluation of 1968 (ref 1).  the          58 1451     
 leapr module of njoy was used for the calculation, and             58 1451     
 the alpha and beta grids were extended slightly.  constants        58 1451     
 that match the endf/b-vi values were used.                         58 1451     
                                                                    58 1451     
 Theory                                                             58 1451     
 ------                                                             58 1451     
 the lattice dynamics of zrh were computed from a central           58 1451     
 force model.  the slightly tetragonal lattice of zrh_2 was         58 1451     
 approximated by a face-centered-cubic lattice.  four force         58 1451     
 constants (mu, gamma, nu, and delta) were introduced describing    58 1451     
 respectively the interaction of a zirconium atoms with its         58 1451     
 nearest neighbors ( 8 h atoms) and its next nearest neighbors      58 1451     
 (12 zr atoms), and the interaction of a hydrogen atom with         58 1451     
 its next nearest neighbors (6 h atoms) and its third nearest       58 1451     
 atoms (12 h atoms).  eigenvalues and eigenvectors of the           58 1451     
 dynamical matrix were calculated, and a phonon frequency           58 1451     
 spectrum was obtained by means of a root sampling technique.       58 1451     
 weighted frequency spectra for hydrogen in zrh were then           58 1451     
 obtained by appropriate use of the dynamical matrix                58 1451     
 eigenvectors (ref. 2).                                             58 1451     
                                                                    58 1451     
 the final values of the four force constants were obtained         58 1451     
 by fitting both specific heat and neutron data.  the               58 1451     
 position of an optical peak observed by neutron scattering         58 1451     
 techniques to be centered roughly around 0.14 ev determines        58 1451     
 the constant mu, while the overall width and shape of this         58 1451     
 peak determine nu and delta respectively.  existing neutron        58 1451     
 data are not sufficiently precise to confirm the structure         58 1451     
 predicted in the optical peak by the central force model.          58 1451     
 specific heat data were used to determine the force                58 1451     
 constant gamma, which primarily determines the upper               58 1451     
 limit on the phonon energies associated with acoustic modes.       58 1451     
                                                                    58 1451     
 References                                                         58 1451     
 ----------                                                         58 1451     
